The paper deals with the detection of backchannel cues in human-computer interaction using acoustic input features. This falls under the sub-category of Speech and Dialogue Processing (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper also makes use of artificial neural networks for the detection task, which is a common technique in the sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG).
